message: The Growth Serum is your best tool for increasing item value, but be careful not to over-grow. Applying it to 'grown' creates 'super-grown', and to 'super-grown' creates 'ultra-grown', typically boosting value. However, applying it to an 'ultra-grown' item will drastically reduce its value. The Mutation Catalyst consistently resulted in negative values in my rounds, so use with extreme caution or avoid it. Combining items usually adds their values, but combining too many different habitats or 'super-grown' items can lead to 'overcomplicated' items with significant negative values. Aim for 'ultra-grown' items and then combine them carefully. Sometimes, it's better to submit a good score than risk a large negative.

Be cautious with the 'growth serum' after the second application, as a third use on a 'super-grown' item often drastically reduces its value. The 'mutation catalyst' consistently resulted in negative values for me, so I recommend avoiding it entirely unless you're confident of a specific beneficial combination. Avoid combining items that have already been treated with tools, as this also tends to lead to very low values.

message: The Growth Serum is your best friend for increasing value, but know its limits. Use it once or twice on an item (especially combined ones) to get to 'grown' or 'super-grown' for positive value. Going beyond 'super-grown' usually leads to a steep drop into negative values. The Mutation Catalyst seems to always make items negative, so avoid it. Combine items with different 'lives in' features (e.g., land and air) to create 'flying' or 'amphibious' creatures, which tend to have good base values before growing. Don't over-combine items or try to grow 'super-grown' complex items too much, as this often results in 'overcomplicated' items with very low or negative values. Aim for a 'super-grown' creature with 2-3 components and diverse 'lives in' features for the highest positive score.
